The paper proposes a model-based reinforcement learning framework that combines Bayesian modeling of system dynamics with curious iLQR, an iterative LQR approach that considers model uncertainty. The paper focuses on robotics tasks, specifically reaching tasks with 7-DoF manipulators, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as Bayesian modeling and reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions using computer vision techniques for the real robot experiments, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on control and system dynamics suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
